What is Javascript? 

Javascript is a small, lightweight, object-oriented scripting language that connects to objects in host environments and controls them. 

JS on the client-side accesses the DOM (Document Object Model) to handle user interaction 

JS on the server-side can run servers and communicate with databases

JS supports a system of small data types, much more free-form, with less requirements 


What is EcmaScript?

Ecma International standards the language 


What do you need to know?
Some knowledge of how the internet works, and a little HTML. 


